overview: The user wanted to elevate the visual appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. I began by analyzing the
  existing design, identifying areas for improvement in color, typography,
  layout, and form elements. I then implemented a new, calming sleep-themed
  color palette, redesigned the main questionnaire form with decorative elements
  and an improved progress indicator, and completely overhauled the welcome
  screen with feature cards and refined alerts. All 14 form sections were
  updated to use consistent, card-style groupings and theme colors, moving away
  from plain gray boxes. Key UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and
  sliders were also polished for a better user experience. Finally, I addressed
  a console error where  values were being passed to input fields,
  ensuring robust rendering. The outcome is a more professional, cohesive, and
  aesthetically pleasing application tailored for a sleep health assessment.
